---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About picochem and its author.">
  <section class="container about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <em>picochem</em> is a personal project: a small encoder-decoder
        transformer for SMILES↔IUPAC translation, built from scratch first in
        pure NumPy and then with hand-written CUDA kernels. The goal was to
        own every line of the stack — tokenizer, ops library, attention,
        backward pass, kernels — so that nothing about a transformer felt like
        a black box.
      </p>

      <p>
        This site collects the write-ups. It is intentionally low on
        ornament: prose, code, a few figures, and citations. If you find
        anything wrong or unclear, I'd like to hear about it.
      </p>

      <h2>About me</h2>
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Arjun Virk</strong>. <em>(Placeholder — edit this paragraph
        with a short bio: where you study or work, what you care about, and
        anything that gives context to the picochem project.)</em>
      </p>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="mailto:virkvarjun@gmail.com">Email</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Colophon</h2>
      <p class="text-small text-muted">
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>.
        Body text is set in Source Serif 4; headings and UI in Inter; code in
        JetBrains Mono. The accent color is a muted forest green
        (<code>#2d5a3d</code>). The whole site is static and weighs
        approximately nothing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about { padding: 3rem 1.5rem 2rem; max-width: var(--measure); }
  .about h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
</style>
